- Prefer pure functions (fizzbuzzOf) for unit testing and composition.
- Use the combined-check (i % 15 === 0) or concatenation approach; both are functionally equivalent. Choose the concatenation approach if you need to support future expansion of other tokens and prefer composability.
- Use Array.from({ length: N }, (_, idx) => /*fn*/ ) to produce consistent ranges without manual loop bookkeeping when you need a collection result.
- In ESM modules, always include file extension in local imports and avoid assuming __dirname; use fileURLToPath when file-system paths are required.
- Use strict equality for remainder comparisons to avoid truthiness pitfalls (0 is falsy).

